akka.actor.IO

EOF

case class EOF (cause: Option[Exception]) extends Input with Product with Serializable

Part of an Input stream that represents the end of the stream.

This will cause the Iteratee that processes it to terminate early. If a cause is defined it can be 'caught' by Iteratee.recover() in order to handle it properly.

  4. def ++ (that: Input): Input

    Append another Input to this one.

    Append another Input to this one.

    If 'that' is an EOF then it will replace any remaining bytes in this Input. If 'this' is an EOF then it will be replaced by 'that'.
